Are you in fact using a SurtPrefixedDecideRule to limit the crawler to 
the 10+ million (!) sites in your seed set?

(If your seed-derived patterns are only around 25 characters long, 
that&#39;s at least 50 bytes per pattern, meaning your scoping rule alone 
could be a 500MB+ in-memory structure. Every URI discovered -- often 
dozens per page -- is looked up in this sorted structure to determine if 
it&#39;s in-scope or not, when it&#39;s the first rule of a scope.)

Or have you replaced that rule with an accept-all rule, which is common 
in broad crawls?

It&#39;s only for those rules that are built up from the seeds/directives 
that any sort of re-feeding or specification-by-file would be required.

- Gordon

On 1/20/12 9:29 PM, David Pane wrote:
&gt; Thanks Gordon.
&gt;
&gt; In regards to why we would want to add additional seeds during the crawl:
&gt;
&gt; We are planning on adding additional URLs that we harvest from twitter
&gt; tweets (we are downloading a set of tweets directly from twitter not
&gt; through Heritrix). We want the final crawl data to definitely include
&gt; these URLs. We were planning on adding these URLS as seeds. It appears
&gt; that we could be adding as many as 3 million of these URLs as new seeds
&gt; each day. So, I am trying to figure out a workaround so that we will not
&gt; have to continually add the accumulation of these new seeds each time we
&gt; need to restart Heritrix.
&gt;
&gt; --David
&gt;
&gt; On 1/20/12 11:52 PM, Gordon Mohr wrote:
&gt;&gt; On 1/20/12 4:41 PM, David Pane wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Only SURT-prefixes coming from an explicitly configured &#39;surtsSource&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; are restored after a checkpoint-resume. Note that this file is just
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; literal SURTs, not the +/- syntax that can be used in seeds files.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This bug is now in the tracking system as:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; https://webarchive.jira.com/browse/HER-1985
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Until it&#39;s fixed, possible workaround would include:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (1) Always configuring SurtPrefixedDecideRules to use a surtsSource,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; and
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; making sure that surtsSource is kept up-to-date as the canonical
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; list of
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; prefixes to rule-in (for an +/ACCEPT rule) or rule-out (for a -/REJECT
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; rule), before any resumes.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; (a) If add the additional opt-out sites to my &quot;opt-out_blacklist.surt&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt; file as a &quot;+&quot; entry (for rule below). Can I use this rule for the new
&gt;&gt;&gt; seeds but use a &quot;-&quot; entry?
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;!-- ...but REJECT those from a configurable (initially empty) set of
&gt;&gt;&gt; REJECT SURTs... --&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;bean
&gt;&gt;&gt; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.SurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;/&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;surtsDumpFile&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt; value=&quot;${launchId}/negative-surts.dump&quot; /&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;surtsSource&quot;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.spring.ConfigFile&quot;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;!-- DAP opt out path here --&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;path&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt; value=&quot;/bos/tmp15/heritrix_crawl/jobs03/2011-12-23/opt-out_blacklist.surt&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; /&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;/property&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; A &#39;seed&#39; is generally a URI you want to crawl, so you would not
&gt;&gt; usually add a seed (in any way) to a REJECT rule, unless it&#39;s a matter
&gt;&gt; of changing your mind about how it (and URIs that are implied
&gt;&gt; extensions of it) should be treated.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Looking over the code, I see that:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; - when lines are announced from a textual &#39;.seeds&#39; source, the &#39;+&#39; or
&gt;&gt; &#39;-&#39; can affect which of different SurtPrefixedDecideRules notice that
&gt;&gt; line, but in either case, if the line is noticed, it is *added* to
&gt;&gt; that rule&#39;s set of SURT-prefixes
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; - when lines are being processed from a static textual &#39;surtsSource&#39;
&gt;&gt; (either inline ConfigString or disk ConfigFile), only &#39;+&#39; directives
&gt;&gt; are noticed, and the following prefix (or hostname/URI that can be
&gt;&gt; coerced to a prefix) is added to the rule&#39;s set of prefixes
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; This is a bit confusing, but it means the exact same list of &quot;things
&gt;&gt; to block&quot; would be prefixed with &#39;-&#39; if dropped in via a mixed
&gt;&gt; seeds/directives &quot;.seeds&quot; file, but should be naked hosts/URIs (no
&gt;&gt; directive) or preceded with a &#39;+&#39; (if a formal SURT) if supplied as a
&gt;&gt; &#39;surtsSource&#39;.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; (I&#39;m not sure what exactly your question meant but that covers the
&gt;&gt; different possibilities.)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (2) After a checkpoint resume, while crawl is still paused, re-present
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; all previously &#39;done&#39; files (including original seed-set/directives) to
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;action&#39; directory for re-learning.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; Our initial seed list was 10M seeds. Do I need to include this in the
&gt;&gt;&gt; action directory after every restart?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; If your crawl depends on learning a giant acceptable-sites SURT list
&gt;&gt; from the seeds, and you are choosing this (2) workaround, then yes.
&gt;&gt; But most broad crawls *don&#39;t* learn an acceptable set of sites from
&gt;&gt; their seed list, so if that&#39;s the case for your crawl, then *no*,
&gt;&gt; there&#39;s no need to re-present the seeds each time.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; - Gordon
&gt;&gt;
